      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, employing the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage accumulation formulation with k-omega SST turbulence closure, has been assessed as credible for identifying the worst-case flow-speed combination that maximises the relative hemolysis index (RH) among the five specified CPB operating points. The claim encompasses steady-state impeller rotation at 2500–4500 RPM across flow rates of 2–6 L/min. Acceptance is conditioned on RH remaining below 1.0 relative to the predicate device benchmark.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; Class II CPB device; MRL 2; five operating points",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory submission demonstrating that CFD can substitute for exhaustive in-vitro hemolysis testing across the full operating envelope"
    }
  ],
